-
The MacNaughtons fought on the Jacobite side at the Battle of Killiecrankie in 1689, however following the Jacobites‚Äô defeat at the Battle of Dunkeld, the MacNaughtons‚Äô lands were confiscated and given to the Campbells of nearby Inveraray Castle.
-
In the early 20th century Sir Andrew Noble, the physicist and artillery pioneer, bought the Ardkinglas estate, which included Dunderave Castle - by that time in ruins. He commissioned Sir Robert Lorimer to restore the castle which was completed by 1912. Today the castle is in private ownership.
