Since 1887 every single bottle of #glenfiddich began its life here. That's not to say things haven't changed though. Innovation is in our blood and Our Solera 15 is a great example of that. So this #fiddichfriday we celebrate our maverick whisky makers, who do things the Glenfiddich way.

Exemplifying our family‚Äôs tradition of innovation, our 15 Year Old expression is created using a technique pioneered by our Malt Master and its warm, spicy flavours are transformed with the alchemy of the Solera Vat.

Uniquely amongst Scotch whisky distillers, our Malt Master matures our Glenfiddich 15 Year Old in three types of oak cask, sherry, bourbon and new oak, to pervade it with rich fruit flavours and distinct spice and honey notes. He then marries it in our unique handcrafted Oregon pine Solera vat, which is always kept at least half full, to give it a beautiful balance and create a deliciously harmonious, consistent and complex whisky that gets increasingly complex over time.

Our Solera system¬†is the culmination of curious minds and the pioneering spirit of our family. It‚Äôs also the secret behind this whisky becoming the first 15 year old expression to enter the top ten best selling single malts.

Tasting Notes

Colour: Golden, a red hue.

Nose: An intriguingly complex aroma. Sweet heather honey and vanilla fudge combined with rich dark fruits.

Taste: Silky smooth, revealing layers of sherry oak, marzipan, cinnamon and ginger. Full-bodied and bursting with flavour.

Finish: Satisfyingly rich with lingering sweetness.

